---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "@/components/PageIntro.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "@/site.config";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Haley Parks, an AI Product Engineer building personal AI systems, human modeling tools, and adaptive performance systems."
>
  <article class="about-page reading-column">
    <PageIntro
      eyebrow="About"
      title="Hi, I'm Haley"
      text="AI Product Engineer, systems thinker, and bodybuilder building software that understands people."
      meta={[
        "AI Product Engineer",
        siteConfig.location,
        "Human-centered systems",
      ]}
      note="Small note, actual person."
      accent="plant"
      width="reading"
    />

    <div class="about-flow">
      <p>
        My work usually starts with a messy human problem, then turns into
        software, data models, dashboards, automation, or conversational
        interfaces that can be used, evaluated, and improved.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am drawn to systems where the interesting part is not one isolated
        metric, page, or workflow, but the relationships between them. Context
        matters. History matters. Goals change. Good tools should help people
        notice those patterns instead of asking them to hold everything in their
        heads.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        Give the machines the burden of remembering, coordinating, searching,
        and connecting. Give people their attention back.
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I am also a bodybuilder. Like many athletes, I wanted a
        deeper understanding of my training than current wearables and fitness
        apps could provide. Recovery metrics are useful, and I rely heavily on
        data from my Apple Watch, but they only tell part of the story.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Human Model began as an attempt to answer those questions for
        myself: how well I am moving, how much force I am producing, how much
        effort a set required, and whether I am creating the training stimulus I
        intended. Along the way, it became a research platform where I can
        experiment with wearable data, biomechanics, machine learning,
        conversational interfaces, and decision-support systems to better
        understand how people adapt over time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="build-beliefs">
      <h2 id="build-beliefs">How I build</h2>
      <ul class="belief-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Systems first, people always.</strong>
          Useful software should preserve context without taking judgment away from
          the person using it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Evidence before claims.</strong>
          I care about interfaces and generated output that can point back to the
          source material behind them.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automation with boundaries.</strong>
          Machines can remember, coordinate, search, and connect; people keep taste,
          direction, and final decisions.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="current-focus">
      <h2 id="current-focus">Current focus</h2>
      <p>
        I am focused on AI product engineering, personal AI systems, adaptive
        performance tools, and human-centered automation. The shared thread is
        software that understands people through context, history, goals, and
        evidence rather than one-off prompts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <aside class="contact-note workspace-object surface-lavender tape-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
      <h2>Open to relevant work</h2>
      <p>{siteConfig.availability}</p>
      <nav class="contact-links" aria-label="Contact links">
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>Email</a>
        <a href={siteConfig.githubUrl}>GitHub</a>
        <a href={siteConfig.linkedinUrl}>LinkedIn</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    margin-block: var(--space-7) var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-flow,
  .about-section {
    max-width: var(--reading-measure);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  .about-flow p,
  .about-section p,
  .belief-list {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  blockquote {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    border-left: 0.34rem solid var(--rust);
    padding: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: var(--font-size-quote);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .about-section {
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-section h2,
  .contact-note h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
  }

  .belief-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .belief-list li {
    border-left: 0.22rem solid var(--khaki);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }

  .belief-list strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .contact-note {
    --object-tilt: 0.2deg;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    border-left: 0.34rem solid var(--houseplant);
    padding: var(--space-5);
  }

  .contact-note p:not(.eyebrow) {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .contact-links a {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
